  "prompt": "Top 10 website makers?",
  "response": "As of my last update, several website builders are highly regarded for their ease of use, features, and versatility. Here is a list of some of the top website builders:\n\n1. **Wix** - Known for its drag-and-drop simplicity and a wide range of templates and apps.\n\n2. **Squarespace** - Offers beautifully designed templates and is popular among creatives for its design-oriented interface.\n\n3. **WordPress.com** - A hosted version of WordPress, it's ideal for blogging and offers a wide range of customization with plugins and themes.\n\n4. **Shopify** - Specifically designed for e-commerce, Shopify is one of the best platforms for online stores.\n\n5. **Weebly** - Known for its user-friendly interface and good balance between customization and ease of use.\n\n6. **Webflow** - Provides more design flexibility and is aimed at designers and developers who want more control over HTML and CSS.\n\n7. **Zyro** - Offers AI-driven tools and a straightforward user experience, appealing to beginners.\n\n8. **Jimdo** - A simple website builder for personal websites and small businesses, with features like an AI-driven setup.\n\n9. **Duda** - Focuses on mobile optimization and is often used by agencies for its client management features.\n\n10. **GoDaddy Website Builder** - Known for its simplicity and integration with GoDaddy\u2019s domain and hosting services.\n\nEach of these platforms has its unique strengths, so the best choice depends on your specific needs, such as the type of website you want to build, your budget, and how much flexibility and customization you require.",
